The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Malls for used vehicles
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Malls for used vehicles
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                          Revankar: Growth move                                  
	Calcutta, May 17: Shriram Transport Finance Company plans to set up at least 10 auto malls in this fiscal to sell used vehicles.         
	A wholly owned subsidiary, Shriram Automall India Ltd, will develop the malls. The 10 malls will entail an investment of Rs 10-15 crore, deputy managing director Umesh Revankar said.         
	Each mall will be set up on three-to-five acres, which will be taken on a lease basis, he said.         
	The first mall will come up in Pune in a months time. Calcutta will get one in the next six months. Plans are on for outlets in Bhubaneswar, Guwahati, Patna, Durgapur and Siliguri in the next two years.        
	Shriram Transport has incorporated another wholly owned subsidiary, Shriram Equipment Finance Company, to offer construction equipment financing.         
	We expect Shriram Equipment Finance to lend Rs 500 crore during the current fiscal and Rs 5,000 crore in three years, Revankar said.                                                                                                                                       
